 2.7.3 - bug fixes and improvements 
https://cvmfs.readthedocs.io/en/2.7/cpt-releasenotes.html#release-notes-for-cernvm-fs-2-7-3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;ARCCE 6.7 (only CentOS7) - enhancements and bug fixes http://www.nordugrid.org/arc/releases/6.7/&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;gfal 2.18.1 - https://dmc.web.cern.ch/release/gfal2-2.18.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;xrootd 4.12.4 - some major big fixes, see release notes: https://github.com/xrootd/xrootd/blob/v4.12.4/docs/ReleaseNotes.txt&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;nagios-probe-bdii 1.0.16&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;nagios-cream 1.2.5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;nagios-plugins-egi-notebooks 0.2.4&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

item.releaseNotes:
This release contains the following products: 
CentOS 7
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Frontier-Squid 2.7.STABLE9-24.2&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;dCache 2.13.28&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scientific Linux 6&lt;/b&gt;This is the first release of UMD4 supporting SL6. It is derived from UMD 3.14.1, mirroring a set of products that are known to be supported and used. More packages will be added, and new upgrades will be available, with minor updates in the next weeks.The products included, grouped by capabilities, so far are: Accounting&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;APEL SSM 2.1.5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;APEL 1.4.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Information system&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;site BDII 1.2.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;top BDII 1.1.4&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Credential management&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;MyProxy 6.1.15&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;GridSite&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;canl 2.2.6&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;emi-wn 3.1.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;emi-ui 3.1.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Client tools&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;dCache SRM Client 2.2.27&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;srm-ifce 1.23.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;CGSI-gSOAP 1.3.8&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;gfal2-plugin-xrootd 0.4.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;gfal2-utils 1.2.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;dpm-argus 1.8.10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Storage Management&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;xroot 4.2.3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;DPM 1.8.10&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;StoRM 1.11.11&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Job execution&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Globus Gram5 6.1.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Job scheduling&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;cream 1.16.5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;cream-ge 2.3.2&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;ARC 15.03.4&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;WMS utils 3.6.6&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Authentication&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;globus-default-security 6.2.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;File transfer&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Globus GridFTP 9.1.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;FTS 3.3.1&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;File access&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;CernVM FS 2.1.20&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;File Access, File Transfer&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;glexec 1.2.3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Frontier-Squid 2.7.STABLE9-24.2&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Attribute Authority&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;VOMS client 3.0.6&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Data access&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;davix 0.5.0&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Authorization&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;argus-pap 1.6.4&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

This release contains the following products:Job execution:&amp;nbsp;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;ARC &lt;/b&gt;v. 13.11.1 released in SL5, and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a minor release, fixing a number of bugs and introducing several new features like Rucio or Axix. Some components were deprecated ( arc-ur-logger, GACL-related and DQ2 DMC) and some are replaced by new commands.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;File Access, File Transfer, Storage Management:
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;DPM&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.8.8 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release provides some new features which were required for the recompilation of many plugins together with a new DB connection pooling indmlite-adapter and mysql which prevents a deadlock under load of dpm-xrootd andwebdav. Also several bug fixes and improvements are adressed namely those related with the mountpoints /dpm.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Job Scheduling:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;GridWay&lt;/b&gt; v. 5.14.2 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a repackaged release due to some missing dependencies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;WMS&lt;/b&gt; v. 3.6.4 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This is a bug fix release which solves the problem of the&amp;nbsp; job submission fails when job ID starts with a dash and WMS callout to LCMAPS.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Client Tools:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;CREAM-UI&lt;/b&gt; v.1.15.3 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This release fixes some minor issues namelly one with the glite-ce-job-output and glite-ce-job-status.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;dCache-srmclient&lt;/b&gt; v. 2.2.22 released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;This release provides support for SHA2 certificates and it now uses by default jblovus 2.0. Migrating to this version of SRM Client is therefore recommended. This release also solves the jumbo proxy issue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Metadata Catalogue:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;LFC&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.8.8&amp;nbsp; released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;No new features or improvements; released from the same source code as DPM 1.8.8&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Other:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;BDII core&lt;/b&gt; v. 1.5.7&amp;nbsp; released in SL5 and SL6:&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;This re